  <sect1 id="intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
&title; is a project to create a complete structured information authoring,
management, archival, revision control and transformation system. &title;
uses XML semantics and powerful graphical editing, coupled with a centralised
storage model and a flexible transformation language to create an environment
which is easy to use, produces high-quality structured output, and lets the user
target several output media with a single source document. 
    </para>      
  </sect1>      
  <sect1 id="getting-started">
    <title>Getting Started</title>
    <sect2 id="to-start">
      <title>To Start &title;</title>
      <para>You can start <application>&title;</application> in the following ways:</para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><guimenu>Applications</guimenu> menu</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>Choose
              <menuchoice>
                <guisubmenu>Accessories</guisubmenu>
                <guimenuitem>XML Editor</guimenuitem>
              </menuchoice>. </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Command line</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>Type <command>&app;</command>, then press <keycap>Return</keycap>.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </sect2>

    <sect2 id="new-document">
      <title>Creating a new document</title>
      <para>
        To create a new document select <guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem> from the
<guimenu>File</guimenu> menu. This will open the Create a new file wizard.
      </para>
